Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Vibrant location with easy access to CBD
Close to train station & Yagan Square

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
120 Roe Street is a unique 3 level building occupying a vibrant location that offers convenient access into the heart of the CBD and walking distance to the Perth central train station.

The building is opposite the new Kings Square office precinct which forms part of the $5.2 billion Perth City Link including Yagan Square, the new underground bus port and Perth Arena.

The third floor tenancy is a unique loft style area with character and architectural design elements including:

•	3 bay sawtooth roof
•	Soaring ceiling heights
•	Large south facing windows
•	Large triangular steel trusses (when exposed they really are very impressive)
•	The interior perimeter walls are largely intact and if exposed are red brick

The building has been refurbished and upgraded to a high standard including: 

- large new lift
- new and efficient air conditioning system
- new bath rooms and kitchen
- new energy efficient T5 lighting
- new carpets
- new 'End of Trip' facilities
- façade refurbishment
- new lobby and entry statement

Other features include:

• Close to freeway on / off ramps and Graham Farmer Freeway
• Vibrant and exciting area with over 200 cafes, restaurant and   bars on your doorstep
• Proximity to William Street and Perth Cultural precinct
• Outstanding City views
